<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="56" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,151,578]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,322,431,457]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">Remarks:</emphasis>
Although, 
<taxonomicName box="[454,746,432,457]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Allokotarsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundicollis">
<emphasis box="[454,746,432,457]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">Allokotarsa rotundicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was first listed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Peringuey" box="[970,1219,432,458]" pageId="3" pageNumber="61" refString="Peringuey, L. (1904) Descriptive catalogue of the Coleoptera of South Africa. (Lucanidae and Scarabaeidae). Transactions of the South African Philosophical Society, 13, 1 - 293." type="journal article" year="1904">
Péringuey (
<number box="[1104,1168,432,458]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" value="1904.0">1904</number>
: 
<number box="[1179,1209,432,458]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" value="37.0">37</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
I decided that it is more appropriate to designate the second species, 
<taxonomicName box="[735,978,472,497]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Allokotarsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clypeata">
<emphasis box="[735,978,472,497]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">Allokotarsa clypeata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as the 
<typeStatus box="[1066,1117,472,498]" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">type</typeStatus>
since it has more representative characters for the genus. For example, 
<taxonomicName box="[678,809,512,537]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Allokotarsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clypeata">
<emphasis box="[678,809,512,537]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">A. clypeata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
does not have the obsolete posterior angles of pronotum which is an autapomorphy of 
<taxonomicName box="[553,734,552,577]" class="Insecta" family="Melolonthidae" genus="Allokotarsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundicollis">
<emphasis box="[553,734,552,577]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="56">A. rotundicollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
